comments.en: This work is part of the assignment PAC2 of the subject "Representació del coneixement" of the UOC (Universitat Oberta de Catalunya). Spring edition 2021-22/2.

abstract.value: This work is intented to model information about TV series, in particular, we will work on an ontology based on the TV series Game of Thrones. Game of Thrones is the television series created by HBO that adapts the novel saga the Song of Ice and Fire, by George R.R. Martin. The story describes the fight for a throne, the iron throne, forged with the swords of defeated enemies. Seven are the kingdoms of the West and many are the houses that will contest the crown: the heirs, the exiles, the dispossessed and the current regents.

comment.en: Series that have been awarded at least one Emmy

In the series Game of Thrones, the basic geospatial organization is a Kingdom. Several kingdoms are in continuous war in order to achieve power.
In addition, a Kingdom may contain one or several house clans.
Every series has some type of content refered as genre.
A season which has been recorded in Spain.
The main actor is the person who appears is most of the episodes.
The director of a series is the person responsible for the sucessful development of the work. It can be regarded as the project manager of the project.
Season consists of a set of episodes of a series. Episodes, like seasons, are presented in a given order.
A weapon made from material, e.g. arrows.
A weapon based on an animal attack, such as dragons.
A Part is an abstract class that denotes a Season or Episode of a series.
A long episode is an episode longer than 80 minutes.
A platform is a means by which a series is broadcast to the audience. Further subclasses specialize this concept.
The TVChannel entity in which the series is broadcast.
The Emmy is a special type of award.
An actor is the real physical person that casts a role or character in a series' episode.
Person is an abstract class which represents a physical object.

A series is a piece of artistic work that involves a set of people, has a set of genre and is broadcast to the audience in several languages and media supports. This is the main class of the ontology developed in this work.

The entity Country is used to link the geographical region in which every season is recorded.
This class shall be defined as an extensive enumeration of instances.
An sporadic actor is a person that solely appears in one or a few episodes, sometimes as a guest actor.
In the series Game of Thrones, every Kingdom has several family houses or clans. This entity is devoted to model these clans.
An award is a prize given to a series.
A character is a role in the series which is cast by an actor.
The author of a series is the person who invented and wrote the series.
In the numerous battles in the series Game of Thrones, diferent types of weapons are used. In particular, there are weapons based on animals, such as dragons, and material-like ones like arrows.
A weapon is classified as lethal if has a stregth greater than 99%.
In an episode, it appears some battle which involves different clans on either side.
A series is translated into one or more languages. The entity language is defined as a set of instances.
The screen writer is the person which usually adapts the story written by the author into the format of episodes. In addition, he writes the script that the actors must cast.
Episode is a development of some story in a fixed amount of time. Episodes, like seasons, are presented in a given order.
A recurring actor is a person that apears is some of the episodes.
A series may be translated in 1 or more languages.
In Game of Thrones, the seasons are recorded in different regions or countries.
In which episode dies a character
The name or description of the weapon.
The name or description of an award.
The number of views of an episode in millions.
The date in which a physical person is born or a character is created.
Further description of the character besides its fullname given by the property hasPersonName.

The author of the series.
The budget associated to each season. The amount is given in millions of US dollars.
A series is comprised of several parts called seasons.
A battle must involve at least 2 or more house clans.
An actor casts or plays a character. The character appears in the episode of the series.
